      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DIAMONDSAREFOREVER (6) resumes from a spell of two years but showed ability as a juvenile, last seen when runner-up at Listed level at this venue. Readied with a couple of solid recent trials so could make a winning return. MARGIMAC (3) did a good job to come from the back row and finish second last time out, beaten 3 metres at this circuit and distance. That was her second placing in three starts off a spell. Race fit now and she is likely to get the favours from this nice draw. OUR SERAPHINA (5) is on the radar after coming from the back row to be beaten only 2.5m here a week ago. LIL MISS DELIGHT (7) comes off a maiden win at Bunbury. That was just her second start so she has upside. Must be included with the confidence up.",
